                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-30T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 30, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. Your 59, April 27, 5 p.m. Ex-Ambassador Morgenthau has telegraphed the
                    President and Prime Minister of Greece in behalf of Papanastasiou and
                    Caphandaris and the Department has acted on the suggestion contained in your
                    telegram No. 60, April 28, 1 p.m.</p>
                <p>The Department has also permitted news services to learn of the trials, but wide
                    publicity has not been given the information thus revealed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
